#originalTopic=Debate:_Public_insurance_option_in_US_health_care
Public insurance saves many businesses cost of health insurance. Paul Waldman. "The Public Option and the Hope of Health Care Reform". American Prospect. December 23, 2008: "big business and small business can finally be persuaded that a strong public insurance program is in their interest, since it will save them money (their prior opposition to health care reform has always been more ideological than economic)."
